<p>I have json</p>  <pre><code>{ "containers": {     "USER": {         "wifPk": "L2x26xxMmKshontu.....qEMh5TCWyf"         }     } } </code></pre>  <p>I need to read container property <code>USER</code> value as case-insensitive. Because it can be <code>user</code> or <code>USER</code>. Starting Jackson 2.5.0 I know it's possible to deserialize json to class using: </p>  <pre><code>ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();   objectMapper.configure(MapperFeature.ACCEPT_CASE_INSENSITIVE_PROPERTIES, true);   CarInfo info = objectMapper.readValue(data, CarInfo.class); </code></pre>  <p>But I can't use class. My code doesn't work:</p>  <pre><code>privateKey = data.getJson().path("containers").path("user").path("wifPk").asText(); </code></pre>  <p>Is there working solution?</p>